\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. L. italica} Parl., {\i Fl. Ital.}{\b  2}: 309 (1857) ({\i L. spicata} auct., non (L.) DC.). Plant (7-)15-25(-35) cm. Inflorescence oblong-elliptical. Perianth-segments c. 2·5 mm. Anthers much longer than filaments. Capsule (2-)2·3-2·6(-2·8) mm, slightly longer than perianth-segments, oblong-ovoid, brown to blackish. Seeds (1·1-)1·3-1·4(-1·5) mm, brown to rusty brown.{\i  Mountain rocks and alpine grassland. C. part of Balkan peninsula; C. Italy and Sardegna.} Al Bu ?Co Gr It Ju Sa.
