\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. L. pindica} (Hausskn.) Chrtek & Krisa, {\i Webbia}{\b  19}: 6 (1964) ({\i L. bulgarica} subsp.{\i  pindica }(Hausskn.) Chrtek & Krisa). Plant (15-)20-30(-45) cm. Basal and cauline leaves (3-)5-8 mm wide, flat. Inflorescence oblong-elliptical. Perianth-segments c. 2·5 mm. Anthers much longer than filaments. Capsule (2·4-)2·5-2·9(-3·1) mm, ovoid, yellowish- to dark brown, distinctly longer than perianth-segments. Seeds (1·4-)1·5-1·7(-2) mm, brown to rusty brown.{\i  Stony and grassy places. • Mountains of S.W. Jugoslavia and N.W. Greece, and of S. Italy}. Gr It Ju.
