\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. L. hispanica} Chrtek & Krisa, {\i Novit. Bot. Horti Bot. Univ. Carol. Prag.}{\b  1965}: 28 (1965). Plant 6-20(-30) cm. Basal leaves slightly recurved. Inflorescence ovoid, rarely interrupted. Perianth-segments 1·5-2·5 mm. Anthers longer than filaments. Capsule 1·4-2 mm, ovoid, dark brown to blackish, usually slightly shorter than perianth-segments. Seeds 0·8-1·2 mm.{\i  Stony and grassy places. Pyrenees and mountains of Spain.} Ga Hs.
