\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. L. nutans} (Vill.) Duval-Jouve,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Fr.}{\b  10}: 80 (1863) ({\i L. pediformis} (Chaix) DC.). Plant (15-)30-50(-70) cm, laxly caespitose, with long, stout stock. Leaf-sheaths decaying into a brownish fibrous mass; basal leaves 3-6(-8) mm wide, flat. Inflorescence 2-4(-6) cm, with 20-100 flowers, interrupted. Lower bract often longer than inflorescence. Perianth-segments 4-5(-5·5) mm, subequal, dark brown, with wide hyaline margin. Anthers 4-5 times as long as filaments. Style c. 2 or more times as long as ovary. Capsule 4-4·5(-5) mm, ovoid-pyriform. Seeds 2-2·3 mm, pale brown; basal appendage 0·2-0·5 mm. 2n = 12. {\i Open woods, rocks and mountain pastures. • Mountains of S.W. Europe.} Ga Hs It.
\par

